
  Name:  mbtowc
 
  #include <stdlib.h>
  int mbtowc(wchar_t *out, const char *in, size_t size);

  The mbtowc( ) function converts the multibyte character in the
  array pointed to by in into its wide character equivalent and 
  puts that result in the object pointed to by out. Only size
  number of characters will be examined.
  
  Example:
  mbtowc(widenorm, mbstr, 2);

  Related Functions:  mblen and wctomb

